At the moment, you're using `Promise.all()` to wait for all the `getDownloadURL()` calls to complete before returning the result. However, if one of the promises fails, the entire operation will fail, and you won't be able to display any images.

To debug this issue, try logging the error message in the catch block to see if there are any errors thrown by `getDownloadURL()`.

Here's an example of how you can modify the code to handle errors more gracefully:

```
const resultWithImages = results.map(async item => {
  try {
    const imagePath = item.image;
    const imageRef = firebase.storage().ref().child(imagePath);
    const url = await imageRef.getDownloadURL();
    return { ...item, image: url };
  } catch (error) {
    console.log('Error loading image:', error);
    return item;
  }
});

setSearchResult(await Promise.all(resultWithImages));
```

This way, if the `getDownloadURL()` call fails for one of the items, the error message will be logged, and the original item with no image URL will be returned instead of breaking the entire operation.

